Metadata Access
Get max length from field metadata in updateView:
typescript// Model-Driven App: metadata is available
const attributes = context.parameters.value.attributes;
const maxLength = attributes?.MaxLength ?? this.maxLengthOverride ?? 100;
const fieldType = attributes?.Type ?? "SingleLine.Text";
Key attributes available from context.parameters.value.attributes:

MaxLength (number) — the Dataverse column max length
Type (string) — the field type, e.g. "SingleLine.Phone"
LogicalName (string)
DisplayName (string)


Field Type Behaviors
Default (SingleLine.Text, SingleLine.TextArea, Multiple)

Standard text input or textarea
Character counter only
Multiple → render as <textarea> with auto-resize

Phone (SingleLine.Phone)

Show phone icon (Fluent Call icon) on the right side of the input
Icon is a clickable button → triggers tel: link (window.open("tel:" + value))
Only show clickable icon when value is non-empty
Style: icon matches Dynamics 365 native phone field appearance

Email (SingleLine.Email)

Show email icon (Fluent Mail icon) on the right side
Icon is clickable → triggers mailto: link
Add real-time email validation (regex + visual indicator)
Validation regex: /^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]+$/
Show validation state: neutral → valid (green check) / invalid (red warning) as user types
Only validate when field is not empty

URL (SingleLine.URL)

Show link icon (Fluent Open icon) on the right side
Icon is clickable → opens URL in new tab (window.open(value, "_blank"))
Auto-detect and show clickable link behavior when value starts with http:// or https://
If value doesn't start with protocol, prepend https:// when opening


